The paper proposes a method for machine learning using artificial neural networks, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The method involves temporal smoothing and entropy maximization, which are techniques used in unsupervised learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions control applications, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and information filtering, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory).
